    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_ym7peaam">
            <alert>Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_oxs8z8z7">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_gtiogple"><p xml:id="auto_7uh9zdxw">Provide pre-measured circular objects with radii already labelled.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_f1qo61sb"><p xml:id="auto_knb13569">Use simpler numbers (e.g., <m>R = 10</m>, <m>r = 5</m>) for initial practice.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_2oalzcb3"><p xml:id="auto_zrnm37x4">Pair struggling learners with confident problem solvers.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_jqifc45x"><p xml:id="auto_zk8885zq">Provide step-by-step calculation templates.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_cezsyiqk"><p xml:id="auto_wdkjqr6b">Break down the formula into steps: find area of outer circle, find area of inner circle, subtract.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_gyt8ma9d"><p xml:id="auto_shalctut">Allow use of calculators.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_k99mpx8f">
            <alert>On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_fzvm8cyy">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_kpudoqls"><p xml:id="auto_6talhme5">Encourage learners to verify their formula with different circular objects.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_zfpeop7x"><p xml:id="auto_6jqfpntc">Ask learners to explain why we subtract the areas rather than the radii.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_bbpvi4uz"><p xml:id="auto_99aq39s0">Provide mixed practice with different types of annulus problems.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_nz96qjhg"><p xml:id="auto_y7ybv8qh">Challenge learners to solve problems where diameter is given instead of radius.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_53lb7vbq">
            <alert>Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_wi0fdvkf">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_v3xhny0y"><p xml:id="auto_mbhtbkei">Challenge learners to derive the formula algebraically and factorise to <m>\pi(R^2 - r^2) = \pi(R + r)(R - r)</m>.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_epm3ea53"><p xml:id="auto_cav0czi8">Investigate the relationship between the width of the annulus and its area.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_lilvb41r"><p xml:id="auto_7zhx1vaf">Apply the concept to 3D shapes (e.g., volume of a hollow cylinder).</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_p54fsyza"><p xml:id="auto_fvfwpd3u">Solve optimisation problems: Given a fixed outer radius, what inner radius maximises or minimises the annulus area?</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_d4l5pq4p">
            <alert>Extension Activity — Running Track Costing:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_ie9s63iw">
            Refer to Activity 2 (running track with <m>R = 35\,m</m>, <m>r = 30\,m</m>, paint cost Ksh 5 per m<m>^2</m>).
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_bqi8xxzv">
            <alert>Solution:</alert> Area <m>= \pi(35^2 - 30^2) = 325\pi \approx 1\,021.43\,m^2</m>. Total cost <m>= 1\,021.43 \times 5 = </m> Ksh <m>5\,107.14</m>.
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx" />

</subsection>